videos.description: Hassan Haskins puts the Wolverines on the board first with a 29-yard rushing touchdown.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Haskins breaks free for 29-yard Michigan TD) 2019/10/12

videos.headline: Haskins breaks free for 29-yard Michigan TD

videos.description: Shea Patterson connects with a wide-open Luke Schoonmaker for a 25-yard touchdown to increase Michigan's lead to 14-0 over Illinois.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Patterson finds Schoonmaker for easy TD) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Patterson finds Schoonmaker for easy TD

videos.description: Shea Patterson connects with Ronnie Bell on a 71-yard passing play. A few plays later, Patterson finds Nick Eubanks in the end zone to widen Michigan's lead to 28-0 over Illinois.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Patterson's big pass play sets up Michigan TD) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Patterson's big pass play sets up Michigan TD

videos.description: Illinois QB Matt Robinson tosses a pass to WR Josh Imatorbhebhe, who bounces off a tackle and gets into the end zone for the score.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Illinois' Imatorbhebhe bounces off tackle for TD) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Illinois' Imatorbhebhe bounces off tackle for TD

videos.description: Michigan RB Tru Wilson fumbles the ball and Illinois DB Stanley Green recovers. On the ensuing drive, RB Dre Brown rushes into the end zone for a 1-yard TD.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Illinois' fumble recovery leads to TD) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Illinois' fumble recovery leads to TD

videos.description: Shea Patterson tosses a five-yard pass into the end zone and Donovan Peoples-Jones makes a diving catch for the score to extend Michigan's lead.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Peoples-Jones makes diving catch for Michigan TD) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Peoples-Jones makes diving catch for Michigan TD

videos.description: Illinois QB Matt Robinson fumbles the ball and Michigan DL Carlo Kemp recovers it at the one-yard line. On the next play, Shea Patterson keeps it himself for the touchdown.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Michigan's fumble recovery sets up Patterson's TD run) 2019/10/12 ESHEET

videos.headline: Michigan's fumble recovery sets up Patterson's TD run

videos.description: Michigan jumps out to a 28-0 lead, but Illinois storms back to within a possession before the Wolverines pull away late for a 42-25 win.
